{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784241222710744023,"compiled_state":{"alias":"eclectic-spotted-barb","assignee":"","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":3,"unsigned":2},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"e942ffa450a2b2ac5bfd6a2666796cbf359e4134ac44bc7ac8789a0e5eff4b38","event_uuid":"0568fea4-1db0-4f2b-b4b2-99d8b02ff974","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784239407145811001-0568fea4-1db0-4f2b-b4b2-99d8b02ff974"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"2b87bd7a1e5c76e7b336df32a1e01d72c2464a675a57da5f9214fdedb28ee250","event_uuid":"1dbebd4e-83ff-40b7-90f2-610350607b7f","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784240923597094001-1dbebd4e-83ff-40b7-90f2-610350607b7f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"2c7a57af908aa1f17c9d2aa19a6bc51a2cd346c0134ba09a26edfd910e27e1be","event_uuid":"abdf6178-ec74-41fe-940c-cab558c5490d","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784241222710744022-abdf6178-ec74-41fe-940c-cab558c5490d"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-211_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"1324605b-cf60-4d72-a5bd-76239bf4c8a5","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"ROOT CAUSE PROVEN + FIXED (rebar-debug protocol, worktree fix-review-sidecar-race).\n\nMECHANISM (runtime-confirmed): _prune_queue_events (enrich_drain.py) ran a raw UNLOCKED whole-index git rm + git commit, outside the unified store write lock (I5) and with no pathspec. In the [agents] drain child it races locked append_event writes two ways: (1) sweep-and-strand — its whole-index commit sweeps a concurrent writer's staged SIGNATURE/REVIEW_RESULT blob into the prune commit; the writer's own commit then fails 'nothing to commit' and the failure path unlinks the file from the worktree though it is in HEAD; (2) 'cannot lock ref HEAD: is at X but expected Y'. Both swallowed by sidecar.emit (->sidecar_emitted=False) and attest.sign_plan_review (->unsigned). Isolated-store experiment (remote OFF, so branch-divergence excluded): 33/360 concurrent writes swept-and-stranded on buggy code; 0 with the fix. Explains why [dev]-only concurrency did NOT reproduce (no drain => no unlocked committer).\n\nFIX: route the deletion through the canonical locked, pathspec-scoped event_append.delete_events — the exact pattern already applied to the twin prunes plan_review/sidecar.py::prune and overlap/digest_sidecar.py (bug malevolent-emigratory-umbrette). _prune_queue_events was the un-hardened twin. One-function change.\n\nRED->GREEN: new held-out regression tests/interfaces/store/test_enrich_drain_prune_concurrency.py — concurrent locked writers vs the real prune committer must lose zero. RED on origin/main (22/250 lost), GREEN with the fix, mutation-checked (reverting the fix returns it to RED). make lint + make typecheck green; make test running. Fix-safety: restoration (I5), no new dep (delete_events exists), no test weakened.\n\nSIBLING (Step-7 sweep): purge_bridge.py has the same unlocked whole-index commit on the tracker — filed as grassgreen-clotty-duck (discovered_from), lower exposure (manual operator command), separate fix.","timestamp":1784240923597094001}],"created_at":1784239407145811001,"deps":[],"description":"# Concurrent review-plan silently drops the plan-review attestation: enrich_drain._prune_queue_events uses an unlocked whole-index git commit that races locked store writes\n\n## Summary\n\nUnder `[agents]`, every `review-plan` finish triggers the opportunistic enrichment drain, whose\n`rebar.llm.enrich_drain._prune_queue_events` (`src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py:191-207`) stages and\ncommits with a **raw, unlocked, whole-index** `git rm` + `git commit` — taking neither the unified\nstore write lock nor a commit pathspec. Running in the detached drain child concurrently with a\nreview's locked `stage_and_commit` writes, it drops the concurrent writer's event, so a PASS\nreview leaves NO persisted attestation (and no observability sidecar).\n\nThis is the un-hardened twin of bug `malevolent-emigratory-umbrette`, whose fix routed the two\nsibling prunes (`plan_review/sidecar.py:94`, `overlap/digest_sidecar.py:141`) through the locked,\npathspec-scoped `event_append.delete_events`; the enrich-queue prune was missed.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Concurrently run `rebar review-plan` on several DIFFERENT tickets (separate processes), with the\n   `[agents]` extra + a real key (so the enrichment drain is live).\n2. Some PASS reviews return `sidecar_emitted=False` and `verify-signature` → \"unsigned — ticket has\n   no signature\", despite a PASS verdict. Serial runs persist fine.\n\nConfirmed by an isolated-store experiment (remote OFF, so branch-divergence is excluded): 6 locked\n`append_event` writers vs 4 processes calling the real `_prune_queue_events` produced 33/360 writes\nraising `git commit failed while holding lock` (\"nothing to commit\" — the writer's staged blob was\nswept into the prune's whole-index commit — and \"cannot lock ref 'HEAD': is at X but expected Y\"),\nwith all 33 blobs left IN HEAD but UNLINKED from the worktree (sweep-and-strand); worktree-listing\nreaders then report them absent.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n\n- **Expected:** a concurrent write is serialized by the single store write lock (invariant I5); a\n  committed event is durable and visible to readers. \"A push failure never fails the write — the\n  commit stays local\" (CLAUDE.md). A PASS review persists a claimable attestation.\n- **Actual:** the unlocked prune committer sweeps/orphans a concurrent locked write; the review's\n  own commit fails (swallowed by `sidecar.emit` → `sidecar_emitted=False` and by\n  `attest.sign_plan_review` → unsigned), and the swept blob is unlinked from the worktree.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`_prune_queue_events` performs a store write OUTSIDE the unified write lock with a whole-index\ncommit, contrary to `event_append.delete_events`'s contract (`event_append.py:302-307`) and the I5\nsingle-lock invariant (`_store/lock.py:1-24`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py:_prune_queue_events` no longer runs a raw unlocked `git rm` /\n  whole-index `git commit`; it routes through the locked, pathspec-scoped\n  `event_append.delete_events` (mirroring `plan_review/sidecar.py:prune`).\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'subprocess.run.*git' src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py` shows no raw `git commit`\n    in `_prune_queue_events`; `rg -n 'delete_events' src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py` present.\n- [ ] A regression test reproduces the race (RED before the fix) and passes after: concurrent\n  locked writes + the drain-queue prune leave zero dropped/stranded events.\n  - Proving: the new test in `tests/` fails on `origin/main` and passes with the fix; `make test` green.\n- [ ] A sibling sweep confirms no other unlocked `git commit` store-write remains outside the\n  locked path.\n  - Proving: `rg -n \"git.*commit\" src/rebar --glob '*.py'` reviewed; any raw store-commit routes\n    through the locked path or is justified.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass (CI's Verified gate green on the change).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"59213327-be9e-430e-b216-e76feb162841","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"3435-c833-4a43-42ae","ticket_type":"bug","title":"Concurrent review-plan silently drops the plan-review attestation: enrich_drain._prune_queue_events uses an unlocked whole-index git commit that races locked store writes","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["0568fea4-1db0-4f2b-b4b2-99d8b02ff974","59213327-be9e-430e-b216-e76feb162841","5b2b7645-6162-4587-94f4-c68fbc9ae667","1dbebd4e-83ff-40b7-90f2-610350607b7f","abdf6178-ec74-41fe-940c-cab558c5490d"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784241222710744023,"uuid":"f578c8d7-0bc4-486f-9890-953e69dbebce"}